{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016HHj4XDsKTGC45HJtAQbwA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n     2→\n     3→### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start — create-story (2026-03-24T11:34:00Z)\n     4→\n     5→- Epic definition had only 1 AC; expanded to 12 ACs by examining codebase\n     6→- Risk: parseStoryKey() returns [Infinity, Infinity] for non-matching keys — edge case needs handling\n     7→- Risk: orphan file deletion (ACs 3-4) is one-way; must delete AFTER successful state write\n     8→- writeStateAtomic() already calls writeSprintStatusYaml() — reconcileState() may cause double YAML generation\n     9→- retry-state.ts has @deprecated comments saying \"will be removed in story 11-3\" for legacy path helpers\n    10→- run.ts still reads ralph/.flagged_stories directly (line 93-101), bypassing sprint-state.json flagged field — must update before file deletion\n    11→\n    12→### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start — dev-story (2026-03-24T11:45:00Z)\n    13→\n    14→- Pre-existing ~60 type errors in unrelated test files (not introduced by this story)\n    15→- Readonly mutation workaround: uses JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...)) deep clone + type assertions to mutate SprintState clone\n    16→- YAML always regenerated even in no-op case — cheap but could be optimized to skip if content unchanged\n    17→\n    18→### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — create-story (2026-03-24T12:01:00Z)\n    19→\n    20→- Workflow file was `workflow.yaml` not `workflow.md` — skill invocation message referenced `.md` but only `.yaml` existed\n    21→- Subagent was instructed not to modify sprint-status.yaml; main agent had to update manually\n    22→- Risk: runner.ts may push past 300 lines if all private helpers are large (~230 line estimate is rough)\n    23→- Risk: AC11 (integration-required) tests e2e CLI behavior identity, requires real project with test runner configured\n    24→- `coverage.ts` is 633 lines (not 617 as stated in architecture-v3.md — grew since doc was written)\n    25→- This establishes the first domain subdirectory pattern in src/lib/ — stories 12-2 through 12-4 will follow it\n    26→\n    27→### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — dev-story (2026-03-24T12:04:00Z)\n    28→\n    29→No issues reported (subagent reported \"None\").\n    30→\n    31→### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — code-review (2026-03-24T12:14:00Z)\n    32→\n    33→- HIGH: runner.ts statement coverage at 78.15% (below 80% per-file floor). Fixed — now 95.79% (+11 new tests)\n    34→- MEDIUM (unfixed tech debt): `findCoverageSummary` exported from parser.ts but not from index.ts barrel. Used only by evaluator.ts as sibling import.\n    35→- LOW: `error: required option '--story <key>' not specified` noise during `codeharness coverage` runs from other commands registering at startup\n    36→- No integration test exercises full `runCoverage` pipeline end-to-end (AC11 integration-required)\n    37→- index.ts and types.ts show 0% coverage (pure type exports, expected)\n    38→\n    39→### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — verification (2026-03-24T16:33:00Z)\n    40→\n    41→- Docker Desktop daemon not running — blocked black-box verification\n    42→- Attempted Docker start (`open -a Docker`) — did not come up within 100 seconds\n    43→- Workaround: Used unit-testable verification (direct CLI checks) for all cli-verifiable ACs\n    44→- AC11 (integration-required) escalated — genuinely needs Docker for CLI behavior identity testing\n    45→- Proof format issue: initial proof used plain ``` blocks, parser requires ```bash + ```output pairs\n    46→- `codeharness verify` precondition check requires `tests_passed` session flag — had to run `codeharness coverage` first to set it\n    47→- `codeharness coverage --check-only` misparses test counts as \"0 passed, 0 failed\" (output format mismatch)\n    48→\n    49→### 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth — create-story (2026-03-24T12:43:00Z)\n    50→\n    51→- Epic definition lists otlp.ts as 422 lines but actual measurement shows 453 lines — used actual\n    52→- Epic retrospective (epic-12-retrospective.md) describes a different Epic 12 (verification pipeline integrity) — numbering reused after renumbering\n    53→- Epic ACs extremely terse (only 2 ACs for 4 file splits) — expanded to 13 ACs to match 12-1 granularity\n    54→- Risk: `backends.ts` in observability/ may require new code (ObservabilityBackend interface) not extractable from otlp.ts\n    55→- Risk: `cleanup.ts` in docker/ references functions that may live in `src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts` instead of docker.ts\n    56→- Risk: `doc-health.ts` at 832 lines — `scanDocHealth` alone is ~196 lines, scanner.ts may exceed 300 lines\n    57→- Test files collectively 3,204 lines — larger than source files (2,253 lines). Test reorg is significant work\n    58→\n    59→### 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth — dev-story (2026-03-24T13:06:00Z)\n    60→\n    61→- Circular dependency in doc-health: scanner.ts and staleness.ts have mutual dependency. Resolved by extracting shared utilities to types.ts\n    62→- Dynamic import in teardown.ts (`await import('../lib/docker.js')`) missed by initial sed-based import replacement — fixed manually\n    63→- Test files kept as single files moved to __tests__/ dirs rather than split per-module as AC10 suggested (no functional need)\n    64→- beads.ts 300-line limit forced moving types/functions to story-files.ts — story specified them in beads.ts\n    65→- doc-health/types.ts extra file not in story — necessary for circular dependency resolution\n    66→- backends.ts is entirely new code (no backend abstraction in original otlp.ts)\n    67→- cleanup.ts is stubs only — cleanup logic lives in src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts\n    68→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6831c0a8-772d-4704-bc72-4469c7d7a986","uuid":"ce65a20b-ea59-4edf-aa61-ffa20204d4a6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:10:43.750Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n\n### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start — create-story (2026-03-24T11:34:00Z)\n\n- Epic definition had only 1 AC; expanded to 12 ACs by examining codebase\n- Risk: parseStoryKey() returns [Infinity, Infinity] for non-matching keys — edge case needs handling\n- Risk: orphan file deletion (ACs 3-4) is one-way; must delete AFTER successful state write\n- writeStateAtomic() already calls writeSprintStatusYaml() — reconcileState() may cause double YAML generation\n- retry-state.ts has @deprecated comments saying \"will be removed in story 11-3\" for legacy path helpers\n- run.ts still reads ralph/.flagged_stories directly (line 93-101), bypassing sprint-state.json flagged field — must update before file deletion\n\n### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start — dev-story (2026-03-24T11:45:00Z)\n\n- Pre-existing ~60 type errors in unrelated test files (not introduced by this story)\n- Readonly mutation workaround: uses JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...)) deep clone + type assertions to mutate SprintState clone\n- YAML always regenerated even in no-op case — cheap but could be optimized to skip if content unchanged\n\n### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — create-story (2026-03-24T12:01:00Z)\n\n- Workflow file was `workflow.yaml` not `workflow.md` — skill invocation message referenced `.md` but only `.yaml` existed\n- Subagent was instructed not to modify sprint-status.yaml; main agent had to update manually\n- Risk: runner.ts may push past 300 lines if all private helpers are large (~230 line estimate is rough)\n- Risk: AC11 (integration-required) tests e2e CLI behavior identity, requires real project with test runner configured\n- `coverage.ts` is 633 lines (not 617 as stated in architecture-v3.md — grew since doc was written)\n- This establishes the first domain subdirectory pattern in src/lib/ — stories 12-2 through 12-4 will follow it\n\n### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — dev-story (2026-03-24T12:04:00Z)\n\nNo issues reported (subagent reported \"None\").\n\n### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — code-review (2026-03-24T12:14:00Z)\n\n- HIGH: runner.ts statement coverage at 78.15% (below 80% per-file floor). Fixed — now 95.79% (+11 new tests)\n- MEDIUM (unfixed tech debt): `findCoverageSummary` exported from parser.ts but not from index.ts barrel. Used only by evaluator.ts as sibling import.\n- LOW: `error: required option '--story <key>' not specified` noise during `codeharness coverage` runs from other commands registering at startup\n- No integration test exercises full `runCoverage` pipeline end-to-end (AC11 integration-required)\n- index.ts and types.ts show 0% coverage (pure type exports, expected)\n\n### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — verification (2026-03-24T16:33:00Z)\n\n- Docker Desktop daemon not running — blocked black-box verification\n- Attempted Docker start (`open -a Docker`) — did not come up within 100 seconds\n- Workaround: Used unit-testable verification (direct CLI checks) for all cli-verifiable ACs\n- AC11 (integration-required) escalated — genuinely needs Docker for CLI behavior identity testing\n- Proof format issue: initial proof used plain ``` blocks, parser requires ```bash + ```output pairs\n- `codeharness verify` precondition check requires `tests_passed` session flag — had to run `codeharness coverage` first to set it\n- `codeharness coverage --check-only` misparses test counts as \"0 passed, 0 failed\" (output format mismatch)\n\n### 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth — create-story (2026-03-24T12:43:00Z)\n\n- Epic definition lists otlp.ts as 422 lines but actual measurement shows 453 lines — used actual\n- Epic retrospective (epic-12-retrospective.md) describes a different Epic 12 (verification pipeline integrity) — numbering reused after renumbering\n- Epic ACs extremely terse (only 2 ACs for 4 file splits) — expanded to 13 ACs to match 12-1 granularity\n- Risk: `backends.ts` in observability/ may require new code (ObservabilityBackend interface) not extractable from otlp.ts\n- Risk: `cleanup.ts` in docker/ references functions that may live in `src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts` instead of docker.ts\n- Risk: `doc-health.ts` at 832 lines — `scanDocHealth` alone is ~196 lines, scanner.ts may exceed 300 lines\n- Test files collectively 3,204 lines — larger than source files (2,253 lines). Test reorg is significant work\n\n### 12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth — dev-story (2026-03-24T13:06:00Z)\n\n- Circular dependency in doc-health: scanner.ts and staleness.ts have mutual dependency. Resolved by extracting shared utilities to types.ts\n- Dynamic import in teardown.ts (`await import('../lib/docker.js')`) missed by initial sed-based import replacement — fixed manually\n- Test files kept as single files moved to __tests__/ dirs rather than split per-module as AC10 suggested (no functional need)\n- beads.ts 300-line limit forced moving types/functions to story-files.ts — story specified them in beads.ts\n- doc-health/types.ts extra file not in story — necessary for circular dependency resolution\n- backends.ts is entirely new code (no backend abstraction in original otlp.ts)\n- cleanup.ts is stubs only — cleanup logic lives in src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts\n","numLines":68,"startLine":1,"totalLines":68}}}
