{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SqZgNxreF4XwuDDT1X5tiu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 12.2: Split docker.ts, otlp.ts, beads-sync.ts, doc-health.ts\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want all 832/590/453/378-line files split into domain subdirectories,\n     9→So that the entire codebase respects the 300-line limit.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→1. AC1: Given `src/lib/docker/` directory exists, when inspected, then it contains: `index.ts` (under 50 lines, re-exports only), `compose.ts` (startStack, stopStack, startSharedStack, stopSharedStack, startCollectorOnly, stopCollectorOnly), `health.ts` (getStackHealth, getCollectorHealth, checkRemoteEndpoint, isDockerAvailable, isDockerComposeAvailable, isStackRunning, isSharedStackRunning, isCollectorRunning), `cleanup.ts` (cleanupOrphanedContainers, cleanupVerifyEnv — new functions extracted from health/compose if applicable, or empty placeholder if no cleanup logic currently exists) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→2. AC2: Given `src/lib/observability/` directory exists, when inspected, then it contains: `index.ts` (under 50 lines, re-exports only), `instrument.ts` (installNodeOtlp, installPythonOtlp, installRustOtlp, instrumentProject, patchNodeStartScript), `config.ts` (configureOtlpEnvVars, ensureServiceNameEnvVar, ensureEndpointEnvVar, configureCli, configureWeb, configureAgent) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→3. AC3: Given `src/lib/sync/` directory exists, when inspected, then it contains: `index.ts` (under 50 lines, re-exports only), `beads.ts` (syncBeadsToStoryFile, syncStoryFileToBeads, syncClose, syncAll, beadsStatusToStoryStatus, storyStatusToBeadsStatus), `sprint-yaml.ts` (readSprintStatus, updateSprintStatus, appendOnboardingEpicToSprint), `story-files.ts` (resolveStoryFilePath, readStoryFileStatus, updateStoryFileStatus) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→4. AC4: Given `src/lib/doc-health/` directory exists, when inspected, then it contains: `index.ts` (under 50 lines, re-exports only), `scanner.ts` (findModules, scanDocHealth), `staleness.ts` (isDocStale, getSourceFilesInModule, getMentionedFilesInAgentsMd, checkAgentsMdCompleteness, checkAgentsMdForModule, checkDoNotEditHeaders, checkStoryDocFreshness), `report.ts` (formatDocHealthOutput, printDocHealthOutput, createExecPlan, completeExecPlan, getExecPlanStatus) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→5. AC5: Given each file across all four new domain directories (`docker/`, `observability/`, `sync/`, `doc-health/`), when `wc -l` is run on every file, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→6. AC6: Given the old monolithic files (`src/lib/docker.ts`, `src/lib/otlp.ts`, `src/lib/beads-sync.ts`, `src/lib/doc-health.ts`), when the split is complete, then they no longer exist (deleted, not left as stubs) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→7. AC7: Given all consumers that previously imported from `docker.js`, `otlp.js`, `beads-sync.js`, `doc-health.js`, when import paths are inspected, then they import from the new domain directories (`docker/index.js`, `observability/index.js`, `sync/index.js`, `doc-health/index.js`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→8. AC8: Given `npm test` is run after all changes, when it completes, then all tests pass with 0 regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→9. AC9: Given `npx tsc --noEmit` is run after all changes, when it completes, then zero new type errors are introduced <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→10. AC10: Given test files for `docker.test.ts` (524 lines), `otlp.test.ts` (1011 lines), `beads-sync.test.ts` (823 lines), `doc-health.test.ts` (846 lines), when the split is complete, then tests are reorganized under the corresponding `__tests__/` subdirectories within each domain directory <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→11. AC11: Given files inside any domain directory (e.g., `docker/compose.ts`), when cross-domain imports are checked, then no file imports directly from internal files of another domain directory — only through barrel `index.js` re-exports or shared utilities (`state.js`, `output.js`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→12. AC12: Given a user runs `codeharness stack`, `codeharness sync`, `codeharness doc-health`, or any command that exercises docker/otlp/beads-sync/doc-health functionality, when the command executes end-to-end, then observable behavior is identical to before the split (same output, same exit codes, same JSON format) <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    25→13. AC13: Given `src/lib/observability/` is created for OTLP utilities, when its purpose is compared to `src/modules/observability/` (audit module), then the two directories serve distinct concerns: `lib/observability/` is the low-level OTLP configuration utility layer, `modules/observability/` is the static analysis audit module <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→\n    27→## Tasks/Subtasks\n    28→\n    29→### docker.ts split (378 lines -> src/lib/docker/)\n    30→\n    31→- [x] Task 1: Create `src/lib/docker/compose.ts` — Move compose operations: `startStack`, `stopStack`, `startSharedStack`, `stopSharedStack`, `startCollectorOnly`, `stopCollectorOnly`, `isStackRunning`, `isSharedStackRunning`, `isCollectorRunning` and related private helpers (AC: #1)\n    32→  - [x] Import types from sibling files as needed\n    33→  - [x] Import `dockerComposeTemplate`, `dockerComposeCollectorOnlyTemplate` from `../../templates/docker-compose.js`\n    34→- [x] Task 2: Create `src/lib/docker/health.ts` — Move health check functions: `isDockerAvailable`, `isDockerComposeAvailable`, `getStackHealth`, `getCollectorHealth`, `checkRemoteEndpoint` and types: `DockerServiceStatus`, `DockerHealthService`, `DockerHealthResult`, `RemoteEndpointCheckResult` (AC: #1)\n    35→- [x] Task 3: Create `src/lib/docker/cleanup.ts` — Extract any container cleanup logic, or create minimal placeholder with `cleanupOrphanedContainers` and `cleanupVerifyEnv` stubs if no cleanup logic currently exists in docker.ts (AC: #1)\n    36→- [x] Task 4: Create `src/lib/docker/index.ts` — Pure re-export barrel file, under 50 lines (AC: #1, #7)\n    37→  - [x] Re-export all public functions and types from `./compose.js`, `./health.js`, `./cleanup.js`\n    38→- [x] Task 5: Update all consumer imports for docker (AC: #7)\n    39→  - [x] `src/commands/stack.ts` — `from '../lib/docker.js'` -> `from '../lib/docker/index.js'`\n    40→  - [x] `src/commands/status.ts` — update import path\n    41→  - [x] `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` — update import path\n    42→  - [x] `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — update import path\n    43→  - [x] `src/modules/infra/stack-management.ts` — update import path\n    44→  - [x] `src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts` — update import path\n    45→  - [x] `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — update import path\n    46→  - [x] `src/modules/verify/env.ts` — update import path\n    47→  - [x] All corresponding test files that import from docker\n    48→- [x] Task 6: Delete old `src/lib/docker.ts` (AC: #6)\n    49→\n    50→### otlp.ts split (453 lines -> src/lib/observability/)\n    51→\n    52→- [x] Task 7: Create `src/lib/observability/instrument.ts` — Move installation functions: `installNodeOtlp`, `installPythonOtlp`, `installRustOtlp`, `instrumentProject`, `patchNodeStartScript` and type `OtlpResult` (AC: #2)\n    53→  - [x] Import from sibling `./config.js` as needed\n    54→- [x] Task 8: Create `src/lib/observability/config.ts` — Move configuration functions: `configureOtlpEnvVars`, `ensureServiceNameEnvVar`, `ensureEndpointEnvVar`, `configureCli`, `configureWeb`, `configureAgent` and exported constants: `WEB_OTLP_PACKAGES`, `AGENT_OTLP_PACKAGES_NODE`, `AGENT_OTLP_PACKAGES_PYTHON`, `NODE_REQUIRE_FLAG` (AC: #2)\n    55→- [x] Task 9: Create `src/lib/observability/backends.ts` — Create `ObservabilityBackend` interface with Victoria and ELK implementations for query building (AC: #2)\n    56→  - [x] Note: backends.ts may be mostly new code if no backend abstraction exists in otlp.ts today — check current otlp.ts for any backend-specific logic\n    57→- [x] Task 10: Create `src/lib/observability/index.ts` — Pure re-export barrel file, under 50 lines (AC: #2, #7)\n    58→  - [x] Re-export all public functions, types, and constants\n    59→- [x] Task 11: Update all consumer imports for otlp (AC: #7)\n    60→  - [x] `src/commands/teardown.ts` — `from '../lib/otlp.js'` -> `from '../lib/observability/index.js'`\n    61→  - [x] `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — update import path\n    62→  - [x] `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — update import path\n    63→  - [x] All corresponding test files that import from otlp\n    64→- [x] Task 12: Delete old `src/lib/otlp.ts` (AC: #6)\n    65→\n    66→### beads-sync.ts split (590 lines -> src/lib/sync/)\n    67→\n    68→- [x] Task 13: Create `src/lib/sync/story-files.ts` — Move story file operations: `resolveStoryFilePath`, `readStoryFileStatus`, `updateStoryFileStatus` (AC: #3)\n    69→  - [x] Import `BeadsIssue` type from `../beads.js`\n    70→- [x] Task 14: Create `src/lib/sync/sprint-yaml.ts` — Move sprint status operations: `readSprintStatus`, `updateSprintStatus`, `appendOnboardingEpicToSprint`, `OnboardingStoryEntry` type (AC: #3)\n    71→- [x] Task 15: Create `src/lib/sync/beads.ts` — Move sync operations: `beadsStatusToStoryStatus`, `storyStatusToBeadsStatus`, `syncBeadsToStoryFile`, `syncStoryFileToBeads`, `syncClose`, `syncAll` and `SyncResult`, `SyncDirection` types (AC: #3)\n    72→  - [x] Import from sibling `./story-files.js` and `./sprint-yaml.js`\n    73→- [x] Task 16: Create `src/lib/sync/index.ts` — Pure re-export barrel file, under 50 lines (AC: #3, #7)\n    74→  - [x] Re-export all public functions and types\n    75→- [x] Task 17: Update all consumer imports for beads-sync (AC: #7)\n    76→  - [x] `src/commands/sync.ts` — `from '../lib/beads-sync.js'` -> `from '../lib/sync/index.js'`\n    77→  - [x] `src/commands/verify.ts` — update import path\n    78→  - [x] `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` — update import path\n    79→  - [x] All corresponding test files that import from beads-sync\n    80→- [x] Task 18: Delete old `src/lib/beads-sync.ts` (AC: #6)\n    81→\n    82→### doc-health.ts split (832 lines -> src/lib/doc-health/)\n    83→\n    84→- [x] Task 19: Create `src/lib/doc-health/scanner.ts` — Move scanning functions: `findModules`, `scanDocHealth` and types: `DocHealthResult`, `DocHealthReport` (AC: #4)\n    85→  - [x] This will be the largest file — ensure it stays under 300 lines\n    86→- [x] Task 20: Create `src/lib/doc-health/staleness.ts` — Move staleness/completeness functions: `isDocStale`, `getSourceFilesInModule`, `getMentionedFilesInAgentsMd`, `checkAgentsMdCompleteness`, `checkAgentsMdForModule`, `checkDoNotEditHeaders`, `checkStoryDocFreshness` (AC: #4)\n    87→- [x] Task 21: Create `src/lib/doc-health/report.ts` — Move reporting/exec-plan functions: `formatDocHealthOutput`, `printDocHealthOutput`, `createExecPlan`, `completeExecPlan`, `getExecPlanStatus` (AC: #4)\n    88→- [x] Task 22: Create `src/lib/doc-health/index.ts` — Pure re-export barrel file, under 50 lines (AC: #4, #7)\n    89→  - [x] Re-export all public functions and types\n    90→- [x] Task 23: Update all consumer imports for doc-health (AC: #7)\n    91→  - [x] `src/commands/doc-health.ts` — `from '../lib/doc-health.js'` -> `from '../lib/doc-health/index.js'`\n    92→  - [x] `src/lib/scanner.ts` — `from './doc-health.js'` -> `from './doc-health/index.js'`\n    93→  - [x] `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` — update import path\n    94→  - [x] `src/commands/verify.ts` — update import path\n    95→  - [x] `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` — update import path\n    96→  - [x] All corresponding test files that import from doc-health\n    97→- [x] Task 24: Delete old `src/lib/doc-health.ts` (AC: #6)\n    98→\n    99→### Test reorganization\n   100→\n   101→- [x] Task 25: Reorganize `src/lib/__tests__/docker.test.ts` (524 lines) into `src/lib/docker/__tests__/` with files matching source modules (e.g., `compose.test.ts`, `health.test.ts`) (AC: #10)\n   102→- [x] Task 26: Reorganize `src/lib/__tests__/otlp.test.ts` (1011 lines) into `src/lib/observability/__tests__/` with files matching source modules (e.g., `instrument.test.ts`, `config.test.ts`) (AC: #10)\n   103→- [x] Task 27: Reorganize `src/lib/__tests__/beads-sync.test.ts` (823 lines) into `src/lib/sync/__tests__/` with files matching source modules (e.g., `beads.test.ts`, `sprint-yaml.test.ts`, `story-files.test.ts`) (AC: #10)\n   104→- [x] Task 28: Reorganize `src/lib/__tests__/doc-health.test.ts` (846 lines) into `src/lib/doc-health/__tests__/` with files matching source modules (e.g., `scanner.test.ts`, `staleness.test.ts`, `report.test.ts`) (AC: #10)\n   105→- [x] Task 29: Delete old test files after reorganization (AC: #10)\n   106→- [x] Task 30: Update test imports in command test files that mock or import from the old paths (AC: #7, #10)\n   107→\n   108→### Cross-cutting verification\n   109→\n   110→- [x] Task 31: Verify cross-domain import discipline — grep for internal cross-domain imports (AC: #11)\n   111→- [x] Task 32: Run `npx tsc --noEmit` — zero new type errors (AC: #9)\n   112→- [x] Task 33: Run `npm test` — all tests pass, zero regressions (AC: #8)\n   113→\n   114→## Dev Notes\n   115→\n   116→### Current File Sizes (actual measured)\n   117→\n   118→| File | Lines | Target Directory |\n   119→|------|-------|-----------------|\n   120→| `src/lib/doc-health.ts` | 832 | `src/lib/doc-health/` |\n   121→| `src/lib/beads-sync.ts` | 590 | `src/lib/sync/` |\n   122→| `src/lib/otlp.ts` | 453 | `src/lib/observability/` |\n   123→| `src/lib/docker.ts` | 378 | `src/lib/docker/` |\n   124→| **Total** | **2,253** | |\n   125→\n   126→### Current Test File Sizes\n   127→\n   128→| Test File | Lines |\n   129→|-----------|-------|\n   130→| `src/lib/__tests__/otlp.test.ts` | 1,011 |\n   131→| `src/lib/__tests__/doc-health.test.ts` | 846 |\n   132→| `src/lib/__tests__/beads-sync.test.ts` | 823 |\n   133→| `src/lib/__tests__/docker.test.ts` | 524 |\n   134→| **Total** | **3,204** |\n   135→\n   136→### Consumer Inventory\n   137→\n   138→#### docker.ts consumers (13 source files + test files)\n   139→- `src/commands/stack.ts` — isSharedStackRunning, startSharedStack, stopSharedStack, getStackHealth, isCollectorRunning, startCollectorOnly, stopCollectorOnly, getCollectorHealth, checkRemoteEndpoint\n   140→- `src/commands/status.ts` — getStackHealth, getCollectorHealth, isSharedStackRunning, checkRemoteEndpoint, DockerHealthResult\n   141→- `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` — isStackRunning\n   142→- `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — isDockerAvailable, isDockerComposeAvailable, isSharedStackRunning, startSharedStack, startCollectorOnly\n   143→- `src/modules/infra/stack-management.ts` — multiple docker imports\n   144→- `src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts` — isDockerAvailable\n   145→- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — DockerStartResult\n   146→- `src/modules/verify/env.ts` — isDockerAvailable\n   147→\n   148→#### otlp.ts consumers (4 source files + test files)\n   149→- `src/commands/teardown.ts` — NODE_REQUIRE_FLAG\n   150→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — instrumentProject\n   151→- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — OtlpResult\n   152→\n   153→#### beads-sync.ts consumers (4 source files + test files)\n   154→- `src/commands/sync.ts` — syncAll, syncStoryFileToBeads, syncBeadsToStoryFile, SyncDirection, SyncResult, readSprintStatus, updateSprintStatus, appendOnboardingEpicToSprint\n   155→- `src/commands/verify.ts` — updateSprintStatus\n   156→- `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` — syncClose\n   157→\n   158→#### doc-health.ts consumers (5 source files + test files)\n   159→- `src/commands/doc-health.ts` — multiple imports\n   160→- `src/lib/scanner.ts` — findModules, isDocStale\n   161→- `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` — scanDocHealth\n   162→- `src/commands/verify.ts` — completeExecPlan\n   163→- `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` — checkStoryDocFreshness\n   164→\n   165→### Important: observability/ namespace collision\n   166→\n   167→`src/modules/observability/` already exists as the static analysis audit module. `src/lib/observability/` will contain the low-level OTLP configuration utilities. These are distinct concerns:\n   168→- `src/lib/observability/` — OTLP package installation, env var configuration, backend query builders (utility layer)\n   169→- `src/modules/observability/` — Semgrep-based static analysis for missing observability instrumentation (business logic module)\n   170→\n   171→No naming conflict — `lib/` and `modules/` are different architectural layers. Document this distinction in a comment in `src/lib/observability/index.ts`.\n   172→\n   173→### backends.ts Note\n   174→\n   175→The epic definition specifies `backends.ts` with `ObservabilityBackend` interface, `VictoriaBackend`, and `ElkBackend`. Current `otlp.ts` may not contain backend abstraction logic — this may need to be created as new code implementing the interface from architecture-v3.md Decision 5. If no backend-specific logic exists in `otlp.ts` today, create a minimal `backends.ts` with the interface and placeholder implementations. Do NOT over-engineer — just enough to satisfy the split structure.\n   176→\n   177→### cleanup.ts Note\n   178→\n   179→The epic definition specifies `cleanup.ts` with `cleanupOrphanedContainers` and `cleanupVerifyEnv`. Current `docker.ts` may not have these exact functions. Check `src/modules/infra/container-cleanup.ts` — cleanup logic may live there already. If docker.ts has no cleanup functions, create `cleanup.ts` as a minimal file that re-exports from the infra module, or create stubs with TODO comments.\n   180→\n   181→### Import Rules (architecture-v3.md, Decision 4)\n   182→\n   183→- External consumers import from `src/lib/{domain}/index.ts` only\n   184→- Within a domain, files can import from siblings\n   185→- No cross-domain internal imports — use `../docker/index.js`, not `../docker/compose.js`\n   186→- `src/lib/state.ts` and `src/lib/output.ts` are shared utilities — any file can import them\n   187→\n   188→### Dependency Graph Within Each Domain\n   189→\n   190→**docker/**\n   191→- `health.ts` — types only, no internal deps (pure functions + execSync)\n   192→- `compose.ts` — depends on `../../templates/docker-compose.js`, may need types from `./health.js`\n   193→- `cleanup.ts` — may depend on `./health.js` for isDockerAvailable\n   194→- `index.ts` — re-exports from all three\n   195→\n   196→**observability/**\n   197→- `config.ts` — env var helpers, standalone\n   198→- `instrument.ts` — depends on `./config.js` for env var setup, `../stacks/index.js` for provider\n   199→- `backends.ts` — standalone (interface + implementations)\n   200→- `index.ts` — re-exports from all three\n   201→\n   202→**sync/**\n   203→- `story-files.ts` — depends on `../beads.js` for BeadsIssue type\n   204→- `sprint-yaml.ts` — standalone (reads/writes YAML)\n   205→- `beads.ts` — depends on `./story-files.js`, `./sprint-yaml.js`, `../beads.js`\n   206→- `index.ts` — re-exports from all three\n   207→\n   208→**doc-health/**\n   209→- `scanner.ts` — core scanning logic, types\n   210→- `staleness.ts` — depends on types from `./scanner.js`\n   211→- `report.ts` — depends on types from `./scanner.js`\n   212→- `index.ts` — re-exports from all three\n   213→\n   214→### Patterns Established by Story 12-1\n   215→\n   216→Follow the same patterns from the coverage/ split:\n   217→- Barrel index files are pure re-exports, under 50 lines\n   218→- Tests reorganized into `__tests__/` within the domain directory\n   219→- Consumer imports updated to use `/index.js` suffix\n   220→- Old monolithic file deleted (not left as stub)\n   221→- No cross-domain internal imports\n   222→- Do NOT create `AGENTS.md` in domain directories — that's a modules/ convention\n   223→\n   224→### Project Structure Notes\n   225→\n   226→- This is Story 12-2 of Epic 12 (lib/ Restructuring). Story 12-1 (coverage/ split) is the template.\n   227→- Story 12-3 will move business logic from status.ts command to a status module.\n   228→- Story 12-4 will create shared test utilities and fixtures.\n   229→\n   230→### References\n   231→\n   232→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md — Decision 4: lib/ Restructuring]\n   233→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md — Epic 12, Story 12-2]\n   234→\n   235→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   236→## Verification Requirements\n   237→\n   238→- [x] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth.proof.md`)\n   239→- [x] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   240→- [x] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   241→\n   242→## Documentation Requirements\n   243→\n   244→- [x] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   245→- [x] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/12-2-split-docker-otlp-beads-dochealth.md`\n   246→\n   247→## Testing Requirements\n   248→\n   249→- [x] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   250→- [x] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   251→- [x] Coverage target: 100%\n   252→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   253→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WxJciqSN2EMLLyK1wQ7yug","session_id":"6831c0a8-772d-4704-bc72-4469c7d7a986","uuid":"30ca35d5-8943-44f0-92ef-ceff574792e2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:13:48.197Z"}
